      <span class="eyebrow">03. What Nature Play Is</span>
      <h3>The garden, brought inside. <span class="it">Open-ended tools</span> for the nature table.</h3>

      <div class="body">
        <p><span class="dropcap">F</span>ill the Busy Bee Tray with water on Monday and float petals and pebbles. Swap in the Sixth Insert on Friday and it becomes six sorting wells for acorns, seed pods, and dried citrus. Add the Papoose teak scoops, the coconut sieve, the felt daisies and acorns, and a tray becomes a term's worth of provocations. There are no batteries. There are no instructions. The materials are the instructions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars">
